= 2004-11-27 EU Commission Presents Competitiveness Report   =
-->
[ [[SwpatbmbfEn| Universitarian Patent Movement]]
| [[SwpatcecEn| Commission]]
| [[SwpatcninoEn| Patent News]]
]
----

The new EU Commission competitiveness report was presented by Commissioner [[GuenterVerheugenEn| GÃ¼nter Verheugen]].  It measures regional competitiveness by the number of patents granted and by the number of patent administration officers employed by universities.

=== References ===

 * http://europa.eu.int/comm/enterprise/enterprise_policy/competitiveness/doc/comprep_2004_en.pdf
   * Many large paragraphs refer to patent law such as
     * 2.4.1 Public business R&D funding and private patent outcomes  Cross-country comparison and empirical analysis of Germany and Finland
 * [[http://europa.eu.int/comm/enterprise/enterprise_policy/competitiveness/doc/scoreboard_2004_en.pdf|Innovation Scoreboard Report 04]] with silly new innovation indicators such as
   * "Number of Technology Transfer Institutions (TTIs) divided by number of Public Research Organisations (PROs), per country" 
   * and "Number of patents/ high tech patents per million inhabitants"

 * Portal: http://europa.eu.int/comm/enterprise/enterprise_policy/

